I have a set of 2000 passat 15in wheels for my 71 the rears fit fine but the
fronts needed to have the centers opened up a little, a dye grinder works
great for this:) A friend just put on a set of 17in a4 wheels and had to do
the same thing

Ian


> FWIW...
>
> I just tried a set of 16s off my wife's A6 the other day. The bolt pattern
> is correct on these wheels (5x112 iirc), as is the back spacing, but the
> center bore is too small and would have to be enlarged for them to fit
over
> the hubs. Anyway, if you've got the means to modify these a bitt, it might
> be a cool project...
